      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## ğŸ§  What is a Chain?\n",
        "\n",
        "A **Chain** in LangChain is a simple but powerful way to connect multiple components.\n",
        "\n",
        "Each part (called a *runnable*) performs one operation â€” like building a prompt, generating text, or parsing the output.\n",
        "\n",
        "Together, they create a flow from **input â†’ output**."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## âš™ï¸ Example: Simple Chain\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's build a very basic Chain using three components:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. A **PromptTemplate** (creates the message)\n",
        "2. A **ChatModel** (generates a response)\n",
        "3. A **Parser** (cleans the output)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\n",
        "from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define the prompt structure\n",
        "prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_template(\n",
        "    \"Tell me a surprising fact about {scientist}.\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Combine prompt + model + parser into a chain\n",
        "chain = prompt | chat_model | StrOutputParser()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Run the chain\n",
        "response = chain.invoke({\"scientist\": \"Marie Curie\"})\n",
        "print(response)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### ğŸ” Step-by-step explanation\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **ChatPromptTemplate**\n",
        "   - Defines the text pattern: `Tell me a surprising fact about {scientist}`.\n",
        "   - Replaces `{scientist}` with the input value (`Marie Curie`).\n",
        "   - Output â†’ structured prompt ready for the model.\n",
        "\n",
        "   Example:\n",
        "\n",
        "   *â€œTell me a surprising fact about Marie Curie.â€*\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **ChatOpenAI (the LLM)**\n",
        "   - Receives the prompt.\n",
        "   - Generates a natural language response.\n",
        "   - Output â†’ structured chat message like:\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "{\n",
        "  'role': 'assistant',\n",
        "  'content': 'Marie Curie was the first person to win Nobel Prizes in two different sciences â€” Physics and Chemistry.'\n",
        "}\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **StrOutputParser**\n",
        "   - Converts structured output into plain text.\n",
        "   - Extracts only the `content` field.\n",
        "   - Result â†’ clean string ready to display.\n",
        "\n",
        "   Example:\n",
        "\n",
        "   *â€œMarie Curie was the first person to win Nobel Prizes in two different sciences â€” Physics and Chemistry.â€*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## ğŸ§© What does `StrOutputParser()` do?\n",
        "\n",
        "- If the model returns plain text â†’ it passes it through.\n",
        "- If the model returns a structured message (like a ChatModel) â†’ it extracts the main content.\n",
        "- Final result â†’ always a **clean string**."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## ğŸ”„ Visual representation of this chain\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input:**\n",
        "```python\n",
        "{\"scientist\": \"Marie Curie\"}\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "â¬‡ï¸ **PromptTemplate:**\n",
        "```\n",
        "Tell me a surprising fact about Marie Curie.\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "â¬‡ï¸ **ChatOpenAI:**\n",
        "```\n",
        "{'role': 'assistant', 'content': '...'}\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "â¬‡ï¸ **StrOutputParser:**\n",
        "```\n",
        "...plain text response...\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## ğŸ’¡ Why Chains matter\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Modularity:** Each block does one thing well (prompt, model, parser).\n",
        "- **Reusability:** You can swap a single block (e.g., a parser) without changing the others.\n",
        "- **Composition:** Combine small chains into larger workflows.\n",
        "- **Maintainability:** Easier to debug, extend, and explain."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## âœ… Summary\n",
        "\n",
        "A **Chain** is an ordered sequence of processing steps.\n",
        "\n",
        "In this example:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. The prompt is built with a variable (`scientist`).\n",
        "2. The model generates a response.\n",
        "3. The parser returns the result as plain text.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is the foundation of how more complex LangChain pipelines work.\n",
        "\n",
        "In the next notebook, weâ€™ll explore **different types of Chains** and how to combine them effectively."
      ]
    }
